                    <comment id="13204631" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 16:43:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think its strange that tokenizer allows a null reader, but we can forget about that temporarily and nuke this default ctor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then, we can put assert reader != null in the &apos;real&apos; ctor and see which analyzers fail.&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe its only PatternAnalyzer and it could be implemented differently/properly (e.g. make a TokenStream).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then we could also keep our assert.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13204660" author="thetaphi" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 17:15:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I remember this was because of Solr. Some tokenizers in Solr were originally TokenStreams. After we restructured all of them, there is no reason to keep default ctor or allow null at all.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13204689" author="mikemccand" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 17:47:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s an initial patch.  Tests pass, but, it&apos;s hacky to pass new StringReader(&quot;&quot;) to all those test tokenizers... really they should be TokenStreams instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13205460" author="rcmuir" created="Fri, 10 Feb 2012 13:58:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updated patch: i tried to clean up these tests some. I think its good to go now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13205614" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 10 Feb 2012 18:34:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I like CannedTokenStream &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;20&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
